<p lang="en">
	<strong>BC Correio - Web Service</strong>
	<br>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;(last update: January 2014)
</p>

<br>

<p>Web Service is a solution to integrate applications. Through it, any system, written in any language, can connect and query or insert data. It is a pattern of interconnection between heterogeneous systems, which uses the Web and XML as a language for information exchange (data and metadata).</p>
<p>
In this way, financial institutions that have their own systems for query messages can benefited themselves by the integration of these systems with the BC Correio using Web Service. However, the use of Web Service is optional to financial institutions (it is not mandatory). All functionality available via Web Service can also be accessed through the application using the browser. This service is only offered as another channel for interacting with the BC Correio.
</p>
<p>
Note: The costs of access related to BC Correio Web Application and its Web Service will are regulated according to Circular 3913/2018 (http://www.bcb.gov.br/pre/normativos/busca/normativo.asp?tipo=circ&ano=2018&numero=3913) and its updates.
</p>
<p>The following operations are available on the BC Correio Web Service:</p>

<ol>
	<li>ConsultarPastasAutorizadas: returns the folders of messages and the sectors that the user is authorized to to access.</li>
	<li>ConsultarCorreiosPorPasta: returns a list with the headers of messages in a folder.</li>
	<li>LerCorreio: returns the content of a message.</li>
	<li>TransmitirCorreio: transmits the message submitted by the user. To achieve, the user must have permission to convey the message type requested.</li>
	<li>ConsultarComunicacaoGeralDocumentoDivulgacao: returns a list with the headings of general communications and the documents transmitted by the BC Correio.</li>
	<li>LerComunicacaoGeralDocumentoDivulgacao: returns the content of a message sorted as Comunicação Geral or Documento de divulgação.</li>
	<li>ObterAnexo: returns the content of an attachment of a message.</li>
</ol>
<p>For technical information about the Web Service BC Correio, read the document below:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.bcb.gov.br/adm/bccorreio/BcCorreio_ManualWebService.pdf" download="BcCorreio_ManualWebService.pdf" target="BcCorreio_ManualWebService">Webservice tutorial (PDF – 461Kb – Portuguese version)</a></p>
  
  
